"AWSTemplateFormatVersion: \"2010-09-09\"\nDescription: >\n  Arc 11 ? knowledge S3 bucket (luciel-knowledge-prod-ca-central-1)\n  + IAM managed policy for backend/worker task roles. AES256,\n  versioning suspended, all-public-access blocked, no CORS, lifecycle\n  for incomplete uploads + noncurrent versions. Bucket lives in\n  ca-central-1. Architecture v1 ?3.2 + ?4.\n\n# Bucket posture (CFN ignores comments, but they document the\n# architectural intent that the Description block can't carry under\n# CloudFormation's 1024-char limit):\n#\n#  * SSE-S3 (AES256) ? Architecture v1 ?4.2: AWS-managed KMS at v1.\n#  * Versioning Suspended. The knowledge_sources.source_version column\n#    already provides version semantics at the row level; S3 versioning\n#    would just duplicate that and grow cost.\n#  * BlockPublicAccess: all four flags true. Uploads go through the\n#    backend API (presigned URLs or direct PUT through FastAPI); the\n#    browser never talks to S3 directly in v1, so CORS stays disabled.\n#  * Lifecycle: abort incomplete multipart uploads after 7 days;\n#    expire noncurrent versions / delete markers after 30 days.\n#    Objects themselves are NOT auto-expired ? the soft-delete worker\n#    deletes them through the API path so audit + cascade stay in sync.\n#\n# Cutover deploy:\n#   aws cloudformation deploy \\\n#     --template-file cfn/knowledge-bucket.yaml \\\n#     --stack-name luciel-knowledge-bucket \\\n#     --capabilities CAPABILITY_NAMED_IAM \\\n#     --region ca-central-1\n#\n# Stack creates the bucket + the managed policy and attaches the policy\n# to the two task roles. CAPABILITY_NAMED_IAM is required because the\n# policy has an explicit ManagedPolicyName.\n\nParameters:\n  BucketName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-knowledge-prod-ca-central-1\n    Description: >\n      S3 bucket name. Matches ARC11_PLAN.md ?12 verification entry.\n      The matching SSM parameter (/luciel/production/knowledge_s3_bucket)\n      is stamped by the same Step 11 deploy script that runs this\n      stack ? backend + worker task-defs read that param at boot.\n\n  BackendTaskRoleName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-ecs-web-role\n    Description: >\n      Existing ECS task role for the backend (luciel-backend-service).\n      Created in an earlier arc; we only attach a managed policy here.\n\n  WorkerTaskRoleName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-ecs-worker-role\n    Description: >\n      Existing ECS task role for the worker (luciel-worker-service).\n      Created in an earlier arc; we only attach a managed policy here.\n\n  Region:\n    Type: String\n    Default: ca-central-1\n    Description: AWS region for ARN composition.\n\n  AwsAccountId:\n    Type: String\n    Default: \"729005488042\"\n    Description: AWS account id for ARN composition.\n\nResources:\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------\n  # The bucket itself.\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------\n  KnowledgeBucket:\n    Type: AWS::S3::Bucket\n    # DeletionPolicy Retain so an accidental stack delete does not\n    # vaporise customer-uploaded sources. Stack updates that REPLACE\n    # the bucket also retain the old physical resource.\n    DeletionPolicy: Retain\n    UpdateReplacePolicy: Retain\n    Properties:\n      BucketName: !Ref BucketName\n      BucketEncryption:\n        ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration:\n          - ServerSideEncryptionByDefault:\n              SSEAlgorithm: AES256\n            BucketKeyEnabled: false\n      VersioningConfiguration:\n        Status: Suspended\n      PublicAccessBlockConfiguration:\n        BlockPublicAcls: true\n        BlockPublicPolicy: true\n        IgnorePublicAcls: true\n        RestrictPublicBuckets: true\n      OwnershipControls:\n        Rules:\n          - ObjectOwnership: BucketOwnerEnforced\n      # No CORS ? the browser never talks to S3 directly in v1.\n      # Re-add a CorsConfiguration block here if and when we switch\n      # to browser-side presigned PUT for uploads.\n      LifecycleConfiguration:\n        Rules:\n          - Id: AbortIncompleteMultipartUploads\n            Status: Enabled\n            AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload:\n              DaysAfterInitiation: 7\n          - Id: ExpireNoncurrentVersionsAndDeleteMarkers\n            Status: Enabled\n            NoncurrentVersionExpiration:\n              NoncurrentDays: 30\n            ExpiredObjectDeleteMarker: true\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------\n  # Bucket policy: deny non-TLS connections (cheap defense in\n  # depth; AWS recommends this for every customer-data bucket).\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------\n  KnowledgeBucketPolicy:\n    Type: AWS::S3::BucketPolicy\n    Properties:\n      Bucket: !Ref KnowledgeBucket\n      PolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          - Sid: DenyInsecureTransport\n            Effect: Deny\n            Principal: \"*\"\n            Action: \"s3:*\"\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}/*\"\n            Condition:\n              Bool:\n                \"aws:SecureTransport\": \"false\"\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------\n  # Managed IAM policy: minimal CRUD on the knowledge bucket only.\n  # Attached to both task roles (backend + worker).\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------\n  KnowledgeBucketAccessPolicy:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::ManagedPolicy\n    Properties:\n      ManagedPolicyName: luciel-knowledge-bucket-access\n      Description: >-\n        Arc 11 - read/write/delete on the knowledge S3 bucket.\n        Attached to luciel-ecs-web-role (backend) and\n        luciel-ecs-worker-role (worker). No ListBucket grant - every\n        operation is keyed on a known object path (s3_key stored on\n        the knowledge_sources row); a List grant would let a\n        compromised role enumerate other admins' object keys.\n      Roles:\n        - !Ref BackendTaskRoleName\n        - !Ref WorkerTaskRoleName\n      PolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          - Sid: KnowledgeBucketObjectCRUD\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - s3:GetObject\n              - s3:PutObject\n              - s3:DeleteObject\n              # s3:AbortMultipartUpload so the bucket lifecycle\n              # rule (AbortIncompleteMultipartUploads after 7d) can\n              # complete its work without IAM friction, AND so the\n              # backend can clean up its own in-flight multipart\n              # uploads on error.\n              - s3:AbortMultipartUpload\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}/*\"\n\n  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # SQS queues for the embed-worker Celery pipeline.\n  # The DLQ MUST be declared before the main queue so the RedrivePolicy\n  # can resolve its ARN via !GetAtt at template-resolution time.\n  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------\n  KnowledgeDlqQueue:\n    Type: AWS::SQS::Queue\n    Properties:\n      QueueName: luciel-knowledge-dlq\n      MessageRetentionPeriod: 345600\n      SqsManagedSseEnabled: true\n\n  KnowledgeTasksQueue:\n    Type: AWS::SQS::Queue\n    Properties:\n      QueueName: luciel-knowledge-tasks\n      MessageRetentionPeriod: 345600\n      VisibilityTimeout: 30\n      SqsManagedSseEnabled: true\n      RedrivePolicy:\n        deadLetterTargetArn: !GetAtt KnowledgeDlqQueue.Arn\n        maxReceiveCount: 3\n\n  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # IAM managed policy that grants the existing backend + worker task\n  # roles read/send/receive on the knowledge queues. This replaces the\n  # ad-hoc inline-policy patches the live deploy applied via\n  # put-role-policy; attaching a managed policy keeps the role-policy\n  # graph reviewable in one place.\n  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------\n  KnowledgeSqsAccessPolicy:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::ManagedPolicy\n    Properties:\n      ManagedPolicyName: luciel-knowledge-sqs-access\n      Description: >-\n        Arc 11 - SQS access on the knowledge-tasks + knowledge-dlq\n        queues. Backend gets enqueue + read-attrs; worker gets the\n        full ReceiveMessage/DeleteMessage/ChangeMessageVisibility set.\n      Roles:\n        - !Ref BackendTaskRoleName\n        - !Ref WorkerTaskRoleName\n      PolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          - Sid: KnowledgeQueueReadAttrs\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - sqs:GetQueueUrl\n              - sqs:GetQueueAttributes\n            Resource:\n              - !GetAtt KnowledgeTasksQueue.Arn\n              - !GetAtt KnowledgeDlqQueue.Arn\n          - Sid: KnowledgeQueueDispatch\n            Effect: Allow\n            Action:\n              - sqs:SendMessage\n              - sqs:ReceiveMessage\n              - sqs:DeleteMessage\n              - sqs:ChangeMessageVisibility\n            Resource:\n              - !GetAtt KnowledgeTasksQueue.Arn\n              - !GetAtt KnowledgeDlqQueue.Arn\n\nOutputs:\n\n  KnowledgeBucketName:\n    Description: >\n      The S3 bucket name. Reference from the backend / worker\n      task-defs via SSM parameter /luciel/production/knowledge_s3_bucket\n      (stamped by the same deploy script that creates this stack).\n    Value: !Ref KnowledgeBucket\n    Export:\n      Name: luciel-knowledge-bucket-name\n\n  KnowledgeBucketArn:\n    Description: ARN of the bucket, for cross-stack references.\n    Value: !GetAtt KnowledgeBucket.Arn\n    Export:\n      Name: luciel-knowledge-bucket-arn\n\n  KnowledgeBucketAccessPolicyArn:\n    Description: >\n      The managed policy attaching CRUD on the bucket to the two\n      task roles. Useful for audit (which policy granted what).\n    Value: !Ref KnowledgeBucketAccessPolicy\n    Export:\n      Name: luciel-knowledge-bucket-access-policy-arn\n"
